      "name": "All Roads Lead Here",
      "type": "feature",
      "system": {
        "description": "<p>While in the Imperial Court, a PC has disadvantage on Presence Rolls made to take actions that don’t fit the imperial way of life or support the empire’s dominance. </p><section id=\"secret-P8G0DAghe8QgaSZV\" class=\"secret\"><p><em>How does the way language is used make even discussing alternative ways of living difficult? What obvious benefits for loyalty create friction when you try to discuss alternatives?</em></p></section>",
